snippet.textDisplay: Just stumble on this channel and don’t know too much about this YouTuber but. I work in e-commerce and white labeling and this isn’t new. What people need to know, is that this is just poor control of its design protection to soon be produce at mass scale. Typically the workflow for  designing containers or any product is working with a design team for months to even years with many Prototypes/renderings. Once that prototype is at the final stage they pick the selected winner, that design team either has an in-house manufacturer or 95% they out source it with an NDA to get quotes for how much would it cost to make 100,000 pieces/cases/units or whatever amount their team thinks the demand will be based on their analytics. They then Send photos, dimensions, colors, renders and the whole nine yards to make the product to get quotes and estimates, and even options. Options as in I will buy 100,000 pieces at $50,000 but will back out if the first 2 weeks of sales are not doing so good, so the first delivery of 50,000 units will be bought at a premium of 20% from the original 100,000 units for $50,000, which will be $30,000 for 50,000 units and if all goes well the remaining 50,000 units will be bought for $20,000 and these options can be more complex but let’s just use that basic concept. So since the designers are looking for quotes, a factory worker can take photos of these and sell the design to somewhere else or know someone that will buy it. So even if the design team do their part to ensure no one leaks anything, there is no control once it’s send out to get it manufactured. That manufacture can easily say you have no proof we leaked anything and etc etc. that’s why companies like Apple have strict rules with their iPhones of no phones in factories and just have their iphones made in hundreds of parts, then assembled in USA so people don’t get to see the full design of the phone since it’s inside apple already. Even if manny say revolution copies, they can always say or modify it a little different to say it was inspired. Then again that is ruining their branding.... this is really common especially in third world country that don’t follow rules, there was a time where we were designing something and we wanted a better price for our units but they declined, so we found another manufacturer at a better price. But that first manufacturer got butt hurt and leaked out design and we took a hit in our sales, since they were selling them already before our launch. Then again that company could modify it slightly or say it was inspired. Oh look, it sounds soooo similar.
